<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="35" type="etymology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="35">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="35">
Latin. 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">fervens</emphasis>
for very hot, boiling hot. The new species name refers to the very hot temperatures of the Brazilian state of 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Piauí">Piaui</normalizedToken>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="35" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="35">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="35">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Campos-Filho, Taiti &amp; Bichuette" authorityYear="2022" class="Malacostraca" family="Styloniscidae " genus="Pectenoniscus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pectenoniscus fervens" order="Isopoda" pageId="0" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fervens">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">Pectenoniscus fervens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. differs from all other species of the genus in the shape of the male pleopod 2 endopod. Moreover, it differs from 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. pankaru" pageId="0" pageNumber="35" rank="species" species="pankaru">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">P. pankaru</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. in having the antennula bearing six aesthetascs, the dactylar seta stout and in the different shape of the male pleopod 1 and pleopod 3-5 exopods. The new species shows the same number of aesthetascs of the antennula as in 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. morrensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="35" rank="species" species="morrensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">P. morrensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. santanensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="35" rank="species" species="santanensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">P. santanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, from which it differs in the antennal flagellum composed of four articles (three in 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. morrensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="35" rank="species" species="morrensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">P. morrensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. santanensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="35" rank="species" species="santanensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">P. santanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), male pleopod 1 protopod with the distal margin concave (vs. straight in 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. morrensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="35" rank="species" species="morrensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">P. morrensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, almost straight in 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. santanensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="35" rank="species" species="santanensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">P. santanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), male pleopod 4 exopod triangular (vs. subrectangular in 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. morrensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="35" rank="species" species="morrensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">P. morrensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, subquadrangualar in 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. santanensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="35" rank="species" species="santanensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">P. santanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and male pleopod 5 exopod rhomboid and longer than wide (vs. triangular and as long as wide in 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. morrensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="35" rank="species" species="morrensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">P. morrensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, subquadrangular in 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. santanensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="35" rank="species" species="santanensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">P. santanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="35">
The specimens of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Campos-Filho, Taiti &amp; Bichuette" authorityYear="2022" class="Malacostraca" family="Styloniscidae " genus="Pectenoniscus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pectenoniscus fervens" order="Isopoda" pageId="0" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fervens">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">Pectenoniscus fervens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. were found only in the aphotic zone (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. A Gruta da Tapagem (Caverna do Diabo), Acungui geomorphological group B Cylindroniscus flaviae Campos-Filho, Araujo &amp; Taiti, 2017 foraging in the organic matter C surrounding area outside Gruta Toca Coroa do Frade, Casa Nova geomorphological group D aphotic zone of the Toca Coroa do Frade." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1101.79043.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/684900" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">2J</figureCitation>
), in vegetable debris with clay and under rocks, where the humidity was higher than at the cave entrance.
</paragraph>
